</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[317,1270,436,1812]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
– Deviating features of the females: (1) antenna with 31–33 antennomeres (31: 2 ♀, 32: 3 ♀, 33: 3 ♀); (2) first tergite 1.5–1.6 times as long as broad behind; (3) hind femur 5.2–5.5 times as long as broad distally. The male is similar to the female: (1) antenna with 37–40 antennomeres (37: 
<quantity box="[1104,1139,1502,1524]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="m" value="3.0">3 ♂</quantity>
, 40: 
<quantity box="[1186,1222,1502,1524]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" unit="m" value="1.0">1 ♂</quantity>
); (2) first tergite (1.5–)1.6–1.7 times as long as broad behind.
</paragraph>
